hands_on_practices.solution:
We wish to find $\alpha_{IR}\equiv\alpha(\mu_{IR})$ given $\alpha_{UV}\equiv\alpha(\mu_{UV})$ with $\mu_{UV}\!>\!M\!>\!\mu_{IR}$.  The one-loop RGE is
$$
\mu\frac{d\alpha}{d\mu}=\frac{b}{2\pi}\,\alpha^2\,. 
$$
Above the threshold $\mu>M$, 
$$b=b_{light}+b_S=b_{light}+\tfrac13 q^2,$$ 
while below $\mu<M$, 
$$b=b_{light}.$$

1.  General solution for a fixed $b$:
$$
\frac{d\alpha}{\alpha^2}=\frac{b}{2\pi}\,d\ln\mu
\;\Longrightarrow\;
-\frac{1}{\alpha(\mu)}\Big|_{\mu_1}^{\mu_2}
=\frac{b}{2\pi}\,\ln\frac{\mu_2}{\mu_1}
\;\;\Rightarrow\;\;
\frac{1}{\alpha(\mu_2)}
=\frac{1}{\alpha(\mu_1)}-\frac{b}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_2}{\mu_1}\,.
$$

2.  Run from $\mu_{UV}$ down to $M$ with $b=b_{light}+\tfrac{q^2}{3}$:
$$
\frac{1}{\alpha(M)}=\frac{1}{\alpha_{UV}}
-\frac{1}{2\pi}\Bigl(b_{light}+\tfrac{q^2}{3}\Bigr)
\ln\frac{M}{\mu_{UV}}.
$$

3.  Continue from $M$ down to $\mu_{IR}$ with $b=b_{light}$:
$$
\frac{1}{\alpha_{IR}}
=\frac{1}{\alpha(M)}
-\frac{b_{light}}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{IR}}{M}.
$$

4.  Combine and simplify, using 
$\ln\frac{M}{\mu_{UV}}+\ln\frac{\mu_{IR}}{M}=\ln\frac{\mu_{IR}}{\mu_{UV}}$:
$$
\frac{1}{\alpha_{IR}}
=\frac{1}{\alpha_{UV}}
-\frac{b_{light}}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{IR}}{\mu_{UV}}
-\frac{q^2}{6\pi}\ln\frac{M}{\mu_{UV}}
=\frac{1}{\alpha_{UV}}
+\frac{b_{light}}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{UV}}{\mu_{IR}}
+\frac{q^2}{6\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{UV}}{M}\,.
$$

Hence
$$
\alpha_{IR}
=\frac{1}{
\displaystyle
\frac{1}{\alpha_{UV}}
+\frac{b_{light}}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{UV}}{\mu_{IR}}
+\frac{q^2}{6\pi}\ln\frac{\mu_{UV}}{M}
}\,. 
$$
